Intro to Nmap
# What Nmap does
Nmap = Network mapper
It scans open ports, running services, and device on network
**Think: what doors are open on this computer
# Nmap Scanning

Nmap = tool to scan networks and ports

Commands:
nmap 127.0.0.1 → scan local machine
nmap <ip> → scan target
nmap -sV <ip> → show service versions
nmap -p <ports> <ip> → scan specific ports

Key idea:
Open ports = possible entry points
